1
00:00:01,835 --> 00:00:04,213
[theme music playing]

2
00:01:23,250 --> 00:01:25,711
[classical music playing]

3
00:01:26,003 --> 00:01:27,754
-Delete!
-[man screaming]

4
00:01:27,838 --> 00:01:29,756
Delete!

5
00:01:30,382 --> 00:01:31,592
Delete!

6
00:01:31,675 --> 00:01:34,261
[man groaning and choking in agony]

7
00:01:39,766 --> 00:01:42,811
[narrator] The average Japanese adult
would say that Teru Mikami

8
00:01:42,894 --> 00:01:45,188
was a child
with a strong sense of justice.

9
00:01:45,564 --> 00:01:49,318
He was able to distinguish right
from wrong better than any of his peers.

10
00:01:50,152 --> 00:01:52,571
And compared to
the average Japanese person,

11
00:01:52,821 --> 00:01:55,365
Teru had been through
and seen far worse miseries...

12
00:01:55,782 --> 00:01:57,534
and even witnessed death.

13
00:01:58,744 --> 00:02:03,915
[classical music continues playing]

14
00:02:05,375 --> 00:02:08,837
SELECTION

15
00:02:09,087 --> 00:02:15,177
[alarm clock beeping]

16
00:02:16,053 --> 00:02:18,722
[birds chirping outside]

17
00:02:38,909 --> 00:02:44,456
[indistinct chatter]

18
00:02:44,665 --> 00:02:48,293
[kids laughing]

19
00:02:52,714 --> 00:02:56,093
[Teru] In this world,
there is only good and evil.

20
00:02:56,218 --> 00:02:58,970
That was one of the first universal truths
I grasped

21
00:02:59,054 --> 00:03:01,723
from observing the world around me
when I was a child.

22
00:03:02,307 --> 00:03:04,267
Every human being, without exception,

23
00:03:04,351 --> 00:03:07,354
ends up falling into one category
or the other.

24
00:03:09,773 --> 00:03:12,401
Even in those innocent years
of elementary school,

25
00:03:12,526 --> 00:03:14,194
one could not escape that fact.

26
00:03:14,277 --> 00:03:15,779
CLASS REP. THIRD-YEAR GROUP A
TERU MIKAMI

27
00:03:15,904 --> 00:03:18,824
As class president, I strived to achieve
great things for my fellow students.

28
00:03:19,282 --> 00:03:22,619
But there were always enemies,
good against evil.

29
00:03:23,328 --> 00:03:24,788
[clattering]

30
00:03:25,372 --> 00:03:27,582
No, stop! Let go of me, please!

31
00:03:27,708 --> 00:03:28,875
[kids laughing

32
00:03:29,126 --> 00:03:30,377
[panting]

33
00:03:30,460 --> 00:03:33,046
Evil has to be confronted.

34
00:03:33,714 --> 00:03:35,215
[grunting]

35
00:03:35,298 --> 00:03:36,758
-[pencil snaps]
-[boy] Get him!

36
00:03:37,050 --> 00:03:40,470
There were times when it seemed
evil would triumph over good.

37
00:03:41,596 --> 00:03:45,684
But no matter what happened to me,
I felt happy for one reason.

38
00:03:45,851 --> 00:03:47,936
[sniffing] Thank you, Teru.

39
00:03:49,938 --> 00:03:52,357
Hearing those words of gratitude
from the victims

40
00:03:52,524 --> 00:03:55,068
made me want to save them again and again.

41
00:03:56,069 --> 00:04:00,449
For that reason,
I never spared any effort.

42
00:04:00,615 --> 00:04:01,658
And in the end,

43
00:04:01,950 --> 00:04:04,619
I was able to stand up for
my sense of justice.

44
00:04:06,288 --> 00:04:07,456
[kids laughing]

45
00:04:07,956 --> 00:04:09,958
-Yeah! Do it!
-Does this bug you?

46
00:04:10,125 --> 00:04:11,501
[kid laughing]

47
00:04:11,835 --> 00:04:12,961
Huh?

48
00:04:14,045 --> 00:04:15,297
[nervous laugh]

49
00:04:19,301 --> 00:04:20,218
[Teru] But...

50
00:04:20,385 --> 00:04:22,554
that was only true
in the world of children.

51
00:04:27,934 --> 00:04:30,854
Middle school was another matter entirely.

52
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:33,315
The more I confronted evil,

53
00:04:33,398 --> 00:04:35,776
the more enemies I had to face.

54
00:04:36,318 --> 00:04:37,277
[crunching]

55
00:04:38,153 --> 00:04:40,071
Victims would become participants,

56
00:04:40,197 --> 00:04:42,574
and even the people watching
would be influenced by evil

57
00:04:42,699 --> 00:04:44,826
and become enemies themselves.

58
00:04:47,871 --> 00:04:51,124
But for justice to triumph,
it requires action.

59
00:04:52,042 --> 00:04:53,794
So, I realized, to serve justice,

60
00:04:54,085 --> 00:04:55,921
I had to delete evil.

61
00:04:57,297 --> 00:05:01,051
The only person who understood my hopes
and remained my ally

62
00:05:01,134 --> 00:05:03,512
was the woman who raised me on her own.

63
00:05:04,095 --> 00:05:05,222
My mother.

64
00:05:05,972 --> 00:05:09,017
No, rather, it used to be my mother.

65
00:05:12,646 --> 00:05:16,733
Teru, not everything in the world
is going to work the way you want it to.

66
00:05:17,776 --> 00:05:19,194
You have to stop doing this.

67
00:05:19,277 --> 00:05:21,822
There's no reason for you
to suffer so much for your beliefs.

68
00:05:22,322 --> 00:05:24,825
What do you think you're proving
getting hurt like this?

69
00:05:25,784 --> 00:05:27,285
This is plain foolishness.

70
00:05:27,619 --> 00:05:29,746
You have to realize that some things
will never change.

71
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:33,083
[Teru] My mother was wrong.
She didn't side with justice.

72
00:05:34,668 --> 00:05:37,254
She was one of those
who deserved to be deleted.

73
00:05:37,629 --> 00:05:38,630
[tires screeching]

74
00:05:38,713 --> 00:05:40,674
[Teru] That was when the miracle happened.

75
00:05:40,882 --> 00:05:42,008
[tires screeching]

76
00:05:42,259 --> 00:05:43,468
[car crashing]

77
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:46,012
Four of the worst delinquents
from my school

78
00:05:46,096 --> 00:05:48,640
lost control of their car
while they were joy-riding.

79
00:05:49,099 --> 00:05:50,350
They died instantly.

80
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:52,602
One bystander was killed as well.

81
00:05:52,936 --> 00:05:55,647
That bystander was my mother.

82
00:05:57,232 --> 00:05:59,734
In one fell swoop,
all the people I resented

83
00:05:59,818 --> 00:06:01,069
had been deleted.

84
00:06:01,486 --> 00:06:03,405
At first, I was terrified.

85
00:06:03,697 --> 00:06:05,156
I couldn't stop shivering.

86
00:06:06,283 --> 00:06:08,243
But then, it hit me.

87
00:06:08,785 --> 00:06:12,873
With these people out of the picture,
how many others would benefit as a result?

88
00:06:13,415 --> 00:06:15,166
Clearly, their victims were relieved.

89
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:16,418
But, beyond that,

90
00:06:16,626 --> 00:06:19,713
wouldn't everyone in my class
be happier now that they were gone?

91
00:06:21,423 --> 00:06:23,008
And sure enough, I was right.

92
00:06:23,592 --> 00:06:25,927
Our classroom
became a peaceful, joyful place.

93
00:06:28,722 --> 00:06:31,308
There will always be consequences
for evil deeds.

94
00:06:31,391 --> 00:06:33,184
That is the way the world is.

95
00:06:33,810 --> 00:06:35,061
The way it should be.

96
00:06:37,731 --> 00:06:39,900
Evil must be deleted.

97
00:06:41,484 --> 00:06:42,903
[Teru] Now then, let's see.

98
00:06:42,986 --> 00:06:44,863
Are there any more problems
with these records?

99
00:06:44,988 --> 00:06:47,157
-[man] No, they're fine.
-[Teru] With every passing year,

100
00:06:47,324 --> 00:06:49,868
my commitment to justice
only grew stronger.

101
00:06:50,452 --> 00:06:54,122
I saw that there will always be those
who have no reason to exist.

102
00:06:54,831 --> 00:06:58,168
Those whose very existence
is a threat to society.

103
00:06:58,793 --> 00:07:00,962
And the closer they grew to adulthood,

104
00:07:01,129 --> 00:07:03,673
the less likely it was
that they would ever reform.

105
00:07:04,466 --> 00:07:06,593
They could only be deleted.

106
00:07:11,723 --> 00:07:13,016
Mysteriously,

107
00:07:13,308 --> 00:07:15,268
every time I judge someone as evil,

108
00:07:15,518 --> 00:07:17,395
they would soon be taken care of.

109
00:07:18,104 --> 00:07:19,230
Was it coincidence?

110
00:07:19,522 --> 00:07:21,024
Was I special somehow?

111
00:07:21,775 --> 00:07:24,027
In the end, it didn't matter.

112
00:07:24,819 --> 00:07:27,072
Divine judgment
must be brought upon evil.

113
00:07:27,489 --> 00:07:31,952
And if it isn't, then someone must
take it upon themselves to punish evil.

114
00:07:32,202 --> 00:07:33,495
COURTHOUSE

115
00:07:33,578 --> 00:07:35,246
That's why I became a prosecutor.

116
00:07:35,538 --> 00:07:36,581
GUIDE TO JAPANESE SENTENCING

117
00:07:36,665 --> 00:07:39,334
It is the role of the prosecutor
to see that evil is brought to justice.

118
00:07:39,459 --> 00:07:41,169
It was an ideal job for me.

119
00:07:42,879 --> 00:07:43,797
And then...

120
00:07:44,381 --> 00:07:45,256
[gasps]

121
00:07:46,091 --> 00:07:47,175
God came before me.

122
00:07:47,258 --> 00:07:48,593
MASS MURDER OF VICIOUS CRIMINALS

123
00:07:48,718 --> 00:07:52,180
Everything that had been happening
around me wasn't coincidence.

124
00:07:52,514 --> 00:07:53,807
WHO IS THE CRIMINAL KILLER, KIRA?

125
00:07:53,890 --> 00:07:55,100
It was divine justice.

126
00:07:56,685 --> 00:07:59,270
God had been watching me.

127
00:08:01,189 --> 00:08:02,148
[grunting]

128
00:08:02,232 --> 00:08:05,151
God had seen
how I did not surrender to evil.

129
00:08:05,485 --> 00:08:08,697
He reached out his hand
and punished the evil people for me.

130
00:08:09,322 --> 00:08:10,657
Once I realized that,

131
00:08:10,949 --> 00:08:14,077
I started to frequent places
where God was bound to be watching.

132
00:08:14,661 --> 00:08:15,996
And then it happened.

133
00:08:16,246 --> 00:08:18,623
[ominous music playing]

134
00:08:18,748 --> 00:08:20,667
[screaming]

135
00:08:20,792 --> 00:08:24,129
God recognized me, as I had always hoped.

136
00:08:24,337 --> 00:08:28,591
Not only that, but He found me worthy
of sharing His power to eliminate evil.

137
00:08:32,429 --> 00:08:35,015
With this, it doesn't matter
if I can't hear His voice.

138
00:08:35,265 --> 00:08:38,893
I shall figure out what Kira wants
and carry out His will.

139
00:08:39,769 --> 00:08:40,645
Delete.

140
00:08:41,312 --> 00:08:43,231
Delete. Delete.

141
00:08:43,690 --> 00:08:46,776
Delete. Delete. Delete.

142
00:08:46,901 --> 00:08:51,656
Delete. Delete. Delete. Delete.

143
00:08:54,576 --> 00:08:55,618
Delete.

144
00:09:10,508 --> 00:09:13,553
[rapid typing]

145
00:09:14,387 --> 00:09:17,182
[Light] Mikami made the choice
to kill Demegawa himself.

146
00:09:17,265 --> 00:09:18,683
I never requested it.

147
00:09:18,975 --> 00:09:21,686
An understandable move
but now there's no spokesperson.

148
00:09:21,770 --> 00:09:23,396
Kira needs a voice.

149
00:09:23,521 --> 00:09:26,399
At the moment,
I can't make any moves myself.

150
00:09:26,816 --> 00:09:28,276
What will he do?

151
00:09:28,860 --> 00:09:30,570
[Teru] Kira isn't saying anything.

152
00:09:31,112 --> 00:09:33,531
He must be in a situation
where he can't move freely.

153
00:09:33,948 --> 00:09:35,909
But this is an important time for him.

154
00:09:36,076 --> 00:09:39,037
We need a spokesperson
to spread His word to the people.

155
00:09:39,829 --> 00:09:41,623
Then, I will take the initiative.

156
00:09:42,457 --> 00:09:43,625
-[door opening]
-[men] Hmm?

157
00:09:44,042 --> 00:09:45,418
Extra, extra!

158
00:09:45,543 --> 00:09:47,462
There's a new development
in the Kira case!

159
00:09:47,629 --> 00:09:50,131
He's chosen a new spokesperson
to take Demegawa's place.

160
00:09:50,507 --> 00:09:52,133
-Huh?
-Take a look!

161
00:09:52,675 --> 00:09:54,135
[upbeat music playing]

162
00:09:54,719 --> 00:09:56,638
Huh? That woman…

163
00:10:00,975 --> 00:10:02,519
Kiyomi Takada!

164
00:10:02,727 --> 00:10:03,728
[Kiyomi] Good evening.

165
00:10:04,145 --> 00:10:06,397
This is Kiyomi Takada from News 6.

166
00:10:06,773 --> 00:10:08,566
Starting today, it will be my duty

167
00:10:08,650 --> 00:10:11,069
to spread the word of Kira,
accurately and quickly.

168
00:10:11,152 --> 00:10:13,113
From now on, NHN will fairly...

169
00:10:13,196 --> 00:10:16,032
[Matsuda] So he picked
NHN's star newscaster, huh?

170
00:10:16,533 --> 00:10:18,076
Kira's got good taste.

171
00:10:18,201 --> 00:10:20,036
Choosing Takki was a good idea.

172
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:21,913
[Kiyomi] ...will be passed onto him
through me.

173
00:10:21,996 --> 00:10:23,289
[Mogi] There's no mistaking it.

174
00:10:23,373 --> 00:10:25,667
That's the girl
that Light dated in university.

175
00:10:27,669 --> 00:10:29,295
You've moved quickly, Mikami.

176
00:10:29,546 --> 00:10:32,382
However, it won't take them long
to find the connection between us,

177
00:10:32,549 --> 00:10:34,175
which could be a problem.

178
00:10:34,801 --> 00:10:37,262
No, on second thought,
she's not a bad choice.

179
00:10:37,387 --> 00:10:40,265
It's one I never would have considered,
since I already knew her.

180
00:10:40,515 --> 00:10:42,475
This could actually make things easier.

181
00:10:42,934 --> 00:10:44,435
I can definitely use her,

182
00:10:44,561 --> 00:10:47,063
but I'll have to find a way
to contact her soon.

183
00:10:48,648 --> 00:10:49,691
[Teru] Kiyomi Takada.

184
00:10:50,483 --> 00:10:51,818
I had a chance to meet her

185
00:10:51,901 --> 00:10:53,736
when I was on a debate program
she was hosting.

186
00:10:54,696 --> 00:10:57,198
She was a shrewd and fair host
for the most part,

187
00:10:57,448 --> 00:11:00,618
but her attitude changed suddenly
when Kira's name was mentioned.

188
00:11:00,952 --> 00:11:04,330
She had a uniquely rigid sense of justice
that I could identify with.

189
00:11:04,622 --> 00:11:07,333
She hates crimes and social evils
with a passion.

190
00:11:08,001 --> 00:11:10,587
I talked with her privately
several times after that.

191
00:11:11,045 --> 00:11:14,174
She clearly supports Kira,
but it's more than that.

192
00:11:14,716 --> 00:11:16,217
She thinks like Kira.

193
00:11:17,260 --> 00:11:21,306
That makes her the broadcaster most worthy
of being the new voice of Kira.

194
00:11:21,681 --> 00:11:26,769
[tense music playing]

195
00:11:26,936 --> 00:11:28,146
Kiyomi Takada.

196
00:11:28,479 --> 00:11:31,357
It'd be too suspicious for Kira
to choose an ex-girlfriend

197
00:11:31,441 --> 00:11:32,734
as his representative.

198
00:11:32,859 --> 00:11:35,778
And there's been no sign of Light
sending her any messages.

199
00:11:36,696 --> 00:11:38,406
Maybe I'm thinking about this too much.

200
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:42,869
Everyone, I just had an idea.

201
00:11:43,077 --> 00:11:45,747
I was thinking we could make use
of Kiyomi Takada.

202
00:11:46,539 --> 00:11:47,999
To be honest, I know her.

203
00:11:48,082 --> 00:11:51,044
Back in university, she and I
were actually dating for a little while.

204
00:11:51,419 --> 00:11:52,378
Oh?

205
00:11:52,503 --> 00:11:53,755
[Aizawa] So, he admits it?

206
00:11:53,838 --> 00:11:55,757
He has no intention
to hide the connection.

207
00:11:56,132 --> 00:12:00,386
If she's acting as his spokesperson,
she must be receiving orders from him.

208
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,513
She's in contact with Kira somehow.

209
00:12:02,639 --> 00:12:04,599
I think our best bet
is to use that connection

210
00:12:04,724 --> 00:12:06,351
to find a way to Kira through her.

211
00:12:06,851 --> 00:12:08,102
KIYOMI TAKADA CHOSEN AS
KIRA'S SPOKESPERSON

212
00:12:08,186 --> 00:12:10,230
But Takki's probably doing it
because Kira's threatening her, right?

213
00:12:10,313 --> 00:12:12,732
She might be too scared to help us out
with our investigation.

214
00:12:13,066 --> 00:12:14,234
[Aizawa] That's a good point.

215
00:12:14,609 --> 00:12:16,236
I'm not too worried about that.

216
00:12:16,611 --> 00:12:18,196
I know her current cellphone number.

217
00:12:18,279 --> 00:12:21,115
I'm pretty sure that I'll be able
to convince her once we get talking.

218
00:12:21,324 --> 00:12:23,201
She'll meet with me, if I ask her to.

219
00:12:23,284 --> 00:12:24,661
[laughs] Wow.

220
00:12:24,953 --> 00:12:27,288
Listen to this guy! You're the man, Light.

221
00:12:27,747 --> 00:12:29,082
Talking to her will be easy,

222
00:12:29,165 --> 00:12:32,543
but the real challenge will be to get her
to help us find and arrest Kira.

223
00:12:32,919 --> 00:12:36,047
We used to talk about a lot of
different topics while we were in college.

224
00:12:36,130 --> 00:12:37,298
And one thing was clear.

225
00:12:38,258 --> 00:12:40,426
-She worships Kira.
-Huh?

226
00:12:41,135 --> 00:12:44,347
But we might be able
to use that to our advantage.

227
00:12:45,515 --> 00:12:47,600
The police claim they support Kira,

228
00:12:47,725 --> 00:12:50,019
but aren't doing anything
one way or the other.

229
00:12:50,353 --> 00:12:52,063
So I'll reveal that I've joined the police

230
00:12:52,188 --> 00:12:54,482
and ask her what we can do
to help Kira further.

231
00:12:54,649 --> 00:12:56,943
To her, it will sound like a good idea.

232
00:12:57,777 --> 00:12:59,279
We can convince her to assist us

233
00:12:59,362 --> 00:13:01,781
as long as we pretend
it's for Kira's benefit.

234
00:13:02,448 --> 00:13:04,409
Do you think that will go over well?

235
00:13:04,534 --> 00:13:06,911
I'm not entirely sure,
but it's worth a try at least.

236
00:13:07,370 --> 00:13:10,915
I agree. It would be foolish for us
to pass up a lead like this.

237
00:13:11,749 --> 00:13:13,376
In that case, I'll call her tonight.

238
00:13:13,710 --> 00:13:14,794
[men] Light!

239
00:13:15,086 --> 00:13:18,673
If you don't mind, I'd like to listen in
on your conversation with Ms. Takada.

240
00:13:18,798 --> 00:13:20,550
Of course. That's fine with me.

241
00:13:20,883 --> 00:13:22,302
Actually, it's better if you do.

242
00:13:22,552 --> 00:13:24,304
If she lets slip something about Kira,

243
00:13:24,387 --> 00:13:26,806
it would be best if more than one of us
was listening.

244
00:13:27,181 --> 00:13:28,516
Uh, yeah.

245
00:13:28,975 --> 00:13:33,813
[tense music playing]

246
00:13:35,982 --> 00:13:37,066
[phone ringing]

247
00:13:37,191 --> 00:13:38,318
Yes, hello?

248
00:13:38,401 --> 00:13:40,361
[Light] Kiyomi? This is Light Yagami.

249
00:13:40,486 --> 00:13:41,362
[Kiyomi] Light?

250
00:13:42,113 --> 00:13:44,324
[Kiyomi] Hi, it's been a while.
What's going on?

251
00:13:44,615 --> 00:13:47,452
Kiyomi, I have something important
to tell you.

252
00:13:48,077 --> 00:13:49,495
Could we meet somewhere?

253
00:13:49,954 --> 00:13:51,414
I have a favor to ask you.

254
00:13:51,622 --> 00:13:52,790
[Kiyomi] A favor?

255
00:13:53,333 --> 00:13:54,459
Yeah.

256
00:13:54,542 --> 00:13:56,669
I know my timing is pretty bad. I mean...

257
00:13:57,003 --> 00:13:59,255
You're the woman the whole world
is watching right now,

258
00:13:59,339 --> 00:14:00,715
so it might not be possible.

259
00:14:00,882 --> 00:14:03,760
[sighs] Don't play innocent and humble
with me, Light.

260
00:14:03,885 --> 00:14:06,888
You wouldn't have called if you didn't
think it was possible to see me.

261
00:14:07,930 --> 00:14:09,307
-[Light] You're right.
-Huh?

262
00:14:09,932 --> 00:14:11,351
Ever since we graduated,

263
00:14:11,476 --> 00:14:14,145
I wanted to talk to you again,
but I never had the chance.

264
00:14:14,937 --> 00:14:17,815
And now it looks like
our jobs have brought us together.

265
00:14:17,982 --> 00:14:20,610
After so much time,
our paths are about to cross again.

266
00:14:20,985 --> 00:14:23,237
Call me crazy
but I feel like this is fate.

267
00:14:24,697 --> 00:14:26,366
What do you mean, "our jobs"?

268
00:14:26,532 --> 00:14:28,159
[Light] I'm working with the police now.

269
00:14:28,242 --> 00:14:31,913
That was part of what I wanted
to talk to you about... in person.

270
00:14:32,622 --> 00:14:35,541
[Kiyomi] The police aren't doing anything
to defy Kira at this point.

271
00:14:36,959 --> 00:14:40,588
All right, I may be able to help you,
depending on what you're asking for.

272
00:14:41,005 --> 00:14:42,215
I appreciate it.

273
00:14:42,465 --> 00:14:45,635
At the very least, I just want you
to hear what I have to say.

274
00:14:45,968 --> 00:14:48,346
Anywhere. Just us two.

275
00:14:51,682 --> 00:14:52,683
Well, okay then.

276
00:14:52,934 --> 00:14:54,852
After tonight's broadcast has finished.

277
00:14:55,561 --> 00:14:56,687
That sounds perfect.

278
00:14:57,063 --> 00:14:58,523
I'll book a hotel room for us.

279
00:14:59,232 --> 00:15:01,067
[Kiyomi] A hotel room? Are you sure?

280
00:15:02,110 --> 00:15:05,238
The last I heard,
you were still living with Miss Amane.

281
00:15:06,197 --> 00:15:08,366
Are things not going too well
on the home front?

282
00:15:08,991 --> 00:15:10,451
[Light] Well, to be honest...

283
00:15:11,077 --> 00:15:14,997
Misa's just not intelligent enough
to be my partner.

284
00:15:15,873 --> 00:15:17,750
-[Misa] Mochi.
-Yes?

285
00:15:17,959 --> 00:15:19,502
Your cooking is really good.

286
00:15:19,585 --> 00:15:21,963
And I appreciate that you're doing
everything for me,

287
00:15:22,046 --> 00:15:24,215
-but it's been five days now.
-Right...

288
00:15:24,340 --> 00:15:27,260
Light doesn't know about you
hanging around all the time, does he?

289
00:15:27,385 --> 00:15:30,054
I'm beginning to get a really bad feeling
about this whole thing.

290
00:15:30,179 --> 00:15:31,180
-Uh huh...
-I mean,

291
00:15:31,264 --> 00:15:32,974
I know that Light trusts me totally,

292
00:15:33,099 --> 00:15:35,977
but don't you think most people
would start saying I'm cheating on him?

293
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:37,812
Oh, he'd be so jealous!

294
00:15:39,021 --> 00:15:41,607
[Mello] Near and the others told me
that this woman's supposed to be

295
00:15:41,691 --> 00:15:42,692
the Second Kira.

296
00:15:42,942 --> 00:15:46,154
But could it really be
this unbelievably stupid girl?

297
00:15:46,946 --> 00:15:47,822
[crunching]

298
00:15:49,365 --> 00:15:52,493
It seems that Kira still hasn't tried
to contact me yet.

299
00:15:53,119 --> 00:15:56,789
If he's in a situation where he's
unable to contact me even if he wants to,

300
00:15:57,165 --> 00:16:00,877
then the next best thing would be
for him to contact Takada instead.

301
00:16:02,295 --> 00:16:03,171
[clicking]

302
00:16:03,880 --> 00:16:06,299
[Kiyomi] Good evening.
This is the nine o'clock news.

303
00:16:06,674 --> 00:16:09,427
First, I have an announcement
that comes directly from Kira.

304
00:16:09,510 --> 00:16:12,054
His words are to become
the new law of the world.

305
00:16:12,221 --> 00:16:16,017
Kira will never forgive those people
whose existence is a threat to justice,

306
00:16:16,392 --> 00:16:18,895
but he will also not forgive those
who live wastefully

307
00:16:18,978 --> 00:16:20,646
and refuse to use their abilities

308
00:16:20,730 --> 00:16:22,773
to contribute
to the betterment of society.

309
00:16:23,024 --> 00:16:23,900
What?

310
00:16:24,108 --> 00:16:26,277
So Kira's gonna kill lazy people now?

311
00:16:26,486 --> 00:16:27,528
You're kidding me.

312
00:16:27,820 --> 00:16:29,864
[Light] You're taking this too far,
Mikami.

313
00:16:29,947 --> 00:16:32,450
It's too early to be making
those kinds of statements.

314
00:16:32,533 --> 00:16:34,285
I've gotta get a hold of him soon.

315
00:16:35,620 --> 00:16:37,205
Matsuda, how is it?

316
00:16:37,580 --> 00:16:40,708
Good. Audio and video online.
No blind spots.

317
00:16:41,417 --> 00:16:43,711
-Until next time.
-The nine o'clock news is just ending.

318
00:16:44,170 --> 00:16:46,214
Everything's in order.
I'll head back to HQ.

319
00:16:46,297 --> 00:16:47,173
Okay.

320
00:16:47,381 --> 00:16:49,467
[footsteps leaving]

321
00:16:50,092 --> 00:16:51,719
[door opening and closing]

322
00:16:55,264 --> 00:16:59,894
[tense music playing]

323
00:17:04,482 --> 00:17:06,275
[door creaking open]

324
00:17:14,325 --> 00:17:20,581
[soft classical music playing]

325
00:17:22,291 --> 00:17:23,501
I missed you.

326
00:17:23,751 --> 00:17:24,752
[gasps]

327
00:17:25,086 --> 00:17:26,379
[both exclaiming]

328
00:17:27,964 --> 00:17:29,966
[Light] Oh. I'm sorry, it's just...

329
00:17:30,216 --> 00:17:31,467
Anyway, please sit down.

330
00:17:34,679 --> 00:17:35,763
To be honest,

331
00:17:35,972 --> 00:17:38,808
it doesn't seem like that long
since we last saw each other.

332
00:17:42,103 --> 00:17:43,187
[sighs]

333
00:17:45,022 --> 00:17:46,023
[gasps]

334
00:17:52,572 --> 00:17:54,156
What the hell is Light doing?

335
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:55,533
He's not saying anything.

336
00:17:55,658 --> 00:17:57,910
If he just stays silent,
she'll get suspicious.

337
00:17:58,327 --> 00:18:01,706
Come on, don't tell me
you've never been in love before, Ide.

338
00:18:01,789 --> 00:18:03,207
-What?
-How's it going?

339
00:18:03,332 --> 00:18:04,458
The mood's perfect.

340
00:18:04,625 --> 00:18:06,085
That's not what I meant.

341
00:18:06,210 --> 00:18:07,086
Uh...

342
00:18:07,295 --> 00:18:09,964
[phone vibrating]

343
00:18:10,339 --> 00:18:11,549
Please excuse me.

344
00:18:12,550 --> 00:18:13,968
-[gasps] Kira…
-[gasps]

345
00:18:16,220 --> 00:18:17,430
Is it Mikami?

346
00:18:17,888 --> 00:18:19,390
She just said it's Kira!

347
00:18:19,599 --> 00:18:21,309
Kira's contacting her directly?

348
00:18:22,560 --> 00:18:23,769
You should answer it.

349
00:18:23,936 --> 00:18:25,187
[Kiyomi] Um, right...

350
00:18:25,605 --> 00:18:28,608
Hello? No, I'm with a friend right now.

351
00:18:29,525 --> 00:18:30,735
Yes, we're alone.

352
00:18:31,360 --> 00:18:34,238
If luck is on my side,
I can get on the phone myself.

353
00:18:34,530 --> 00:18:36,866
Well, Mikami, can you make it happen?

354
00:18:37,158 --> 00:18:39,160
[Kiyomi] He wanted to meet me
all of a sudden.

355
00:18:40,077 --> 00:18:41,954
[Teru] Someone who requests
a private meeting

356
00:18:42,038 --> 00:18:43,289
with Kira's spokesperson?

357
00:18:44,123 --> 00:18:45,791
I'd like to speak with him, if I may.

358
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:47,126
[gasps]

359
00:18:48,544 --> 00:18:50,254
He said that he wants to speak to you.

360
00:18:50,838 --> 00:18:51,922
Perfect.

361
00:18:52,048 --> 00:18:54,133
I was right to choose you, Mikami.

362
00:18:56,218 --> 00:18:57,762
She's passed the phone to Light.

363
00:18:57,970 --> 00:18:59,680
It could be dangerous
if he's the real thing.

364
00:19:00,514 --> 00:19:01,724
Yes, hello?

365
00:19:02,433 --> 00:19:04,143
[distorted voice] Who am I speaking to?

366
00:19:05,561 --> 00:19:07,647
Five pages on November 26?

367
00:19:07,938 --> 00:19:09,523
I don't get it. What do you mean?

368
00:19:11,734 --> 00:19:12,735
You're God!

369
00:19:13,194 --> 00:19:14,904
You're doing well, Mikami.

370
00:19:15,029 --> 00:19:16,822
Let's just see how much
you can figure out.

371
00:19:17,239 --> 00:19:19,742
[Teru] God, you're not free
to speak right now.

372
00:19:19,992 --> 00:19:20,910
[Light] Yes.

373
00:19:21,077 --> 00:19:22,578
You're being watched at the moment.

374
00:19:22,703 --> 00:19:25,873
Yes. But how I can trust
you're the real Kira?

375
00:19:26,582 --> 00:19:28,751
Is he asking me
to judge someone right now?

376
00:19:28,959 --> 00:19:30,086
Turn to Sakura TV!

377
00:19:30,461 --> 00:19:32,713
What's that? Sakura TV?

378
00:19:33,005 --> 00:19:34,256
Quick! Let's check it out.

379
00:19:35,049 --> 00:19:38,761
We'll invite Kira back to our program,
no matter what it might take.

380
00:19:38,928 --> 00:19:40,179
[groans in pain]

381
00:19:40,596 --> 00:19:43,182
-He died!
-[Ide] This is bad! He's the real thing.

382
00:19:43,557 --> 00:19:44,684
-Mikami...
-[Teru] Yes?

383
00:19:44,767 --> 00:19:47,061
...you're even better than I expected.

384
00:19:47,144 --> 00:19:49,772
KIRA WANTS ROOM CHECKED FOR DEVICES.
I'M REMOVING THEM BEFORE HE SEES THEM.

385
00:19:49,855 --> 00:19:51,440
[Matsuda] What? He's removing the bugs?

386
00:19:51,649 --> 00:19:53,234
We don't have a choice.

387
00:19:56,737 --> 00:19:58,781
[Kiyomi] I don't understand.
What's going on?

388
00:19:59,532 --> 00:20:01,450
Now I can talk without any constraints.

389
00:20:01,784 --> 00:20:02,743
What?

390
00:20:03,536 --> 00:20:04,745
Listen, Kiyomi…

391
00:20:05,663 --> 00:20:06,831
I am the real Kira.

392
00:20:07,039 --> 00:20:07,957
[gasps]

393
00:20:08,582 --> 00:20:10,543
That's right. I'm Kira.

394
00:20:11,085 --> 00:20:12,753
That's what I wanted to tell you.

395
00:20:13,879 --> 00:20:16,382
[Kiyomi] Light is… Kira?

396
00:20:17,717 --> 00:20:20,761
Listen, I won't allow you
to ask Kiyomi who I am.

397
00:20:20,845 --> 00:20:22,346
You don't need to know my identity.

398
00:20:23,139 --> 00:20:26,058
Yes. I'll leave the rest to you, God.

399
00:20:27,351 --> 00:20:28,519
[Light] Do you understand?

400
00:20:28,728 --> 00:20:29,770
I am Kira.

401
00:20:30,438 --> 00:20:31,856
The man who was on the phone

402
00:20:32,022 --> 00:20:34,275
is one of my followers
who I've shared my power with.

403
00:20:35,359 --> 00:20:37,903
[gasps] I can't believe it's you.

404
00:20:38,404 --> 00:20:40,573
You were the only man
I ever really admired.

405
00:20:40,948 --> 00:20:44,243
To be honest, the only man
I ever felt a connection with.

406
00:20:44,785 --> 00:20:46,746
And now, to find out you're Kira...

407
00:20:47,788 --> 00:20:48,998
It's incredible.

408
00:20:51,041 --> 00:20:53,210
[Light] Please, join me, Kiyomi...

409
00:20:53,586 --> 00:20:56,046
and you will be
the goddess of the new world.

410
00:20:57,923 --> 00:20:58,966
Oh, Light...

411
00:20:59,216 --> 00:21:03,387
[dramatic music playing]

412
00:21:05,431 --> 00:21:07,057
-[phone ringing]
-[men exclaiming]

413
00:21:07,475 --> 00:21:08,851
Light, are you okay?

414
00:21:09,310 --> 00:21:12,646
Yeah. Kiyomi was able
to work things out with Kira.

415
00:21:13,022 --> 00:21:16,275
I've decided that from now on,
I'm going to pretend to be dating her.

416
00:21:16,525 --> 00:21:18,319
We might be able to find Kira that way.

417
00:21:19,195 --> 00:21:21,530
[Teru] Delete, delete, delete,

418
00:21:21,906 --> 00:21:23,574
delete, delete,

419
00:21:23,824 --> 00:21:25,785
delete.

420
00:21:26,327 --> 00:21:27,995
Delete!

421
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:33,250
TO BE CONTINUED

422
00:21:38,214 --> 00:21:43,886
[ending theme song playing]
